message.title: Rally 8P
message.text: Welcome to a new 8 players variant of Tetris! This tutorial map is designed to guide you along as you play.

message.title: First Single!
message.text: You have cleared a Single! Let's see what happens when you place a Tetrimino inbetween the red minos.

message.title: Falling
message.text: Due to special gravity, blocks wouldbreak apart and fall down when you clear lines.

message.title: Sticky
message.text: Did you notice same colored blocks stick to each other? Avoid this during the game, so you may get down faster.

message.title: Concrete Blocks
message.text: Unlike the colored blocks, these grey Concrete Blocks do not fall down.

message.title: Ice Blocks
message.text: Ice Blocks are very similar to the Concrete Blocks, except you have to clear them twice.

message.title: Item Blocks
message.text: You will earn an item when you clear the Item Block, which is labeled with a [?].

message.title: Using Items
message.text: You have earned an Item! Items are used automatically, but you can also use them by pressing [V].

message.title: Map View
message.text: This view allows you keep track of other opponents' progress at anytime.

message.title: Item Types
message.text: Items with Blue icon will help you get down faster, while items with Red icon will slow down your opponents.

message.title: Goal
message.text: You are almost there! Place your Tetrimino on top of the Goal to finish the game!

message.title: Game Over
message.text: Like all other Tetris variants, the game ends when you top out of the Matrix. Please try again.

message.title: Item Gauge
message.text: When you are stuck for too long, the Item Gauge will increase. Once it is full, you will earn an item.

message.title: Placement
message.text: This area indicates your current place in the game. First person to finish the race will earn 3 Stars!

message.title: Auto Item
message.text: Clicking on the Auto Item button allows you to manually decide when to use an item.
